rComments: Don't take this course if it is not mandatory. Run!!

She didn't know how to teach you well. The purpose of this course is just to gross you out. You will learn nothing from this course but only some stereotypes to another countries. Extremely dull and catastrophic experience.

Seems sweet, but is so disorganized every good quality flies out the window. Her lectures consist of loaded slides with her narration that only relates to what's actually on the slide about 60% of the time. No sense of direction. Final was closed book and multiple choice (torture). Projects were idiotic and everyone was confused about them. Avoid

Her slides are extremely unorganized, with tons of abbreviations. The TA only followed the official answer to grade your assignment, which means you will get a 0 if you cannot answer in the way they wish you to answer. This course is really boring and tedious. Never take this course if it is not mandatory.

Honestly can't believe her rating. Saw it before I took the class and it freaked me out but she's so funny and entertaining. I learned a lot in her class and anyone that gave her such a harsh rating, just didn't bother to put in any effort. If professor Sharon is reading this: Loved your class and keep doing you!
Her PowerPoints are so disorganized. She does not explain very well. Too much group works and projects. UGH

She doesnt even bother to teach during lectures, you need to watch long and low quality recordings made by her TA during your free time. She doesnt care about her students at all. The most boring and useless class Ive ever taken.

Avoid if possible. Any other professor would be better as she is such a harsh grader and very unclear with her page long explanations. All the projects are not complicated to do but what she requires is so unclear that its easy to flop it. Her TA is also very harsh so avoid her class at all costs if possible.

3 parts for the group project and 1 presn. A single rubric for 1 part was 8 pages. It was not concise at all and seemed not possible to meet all requirements within 8 to 12-page writing. I had a feeling that the TA herself was not clear about the rubric so the grading was bad. I was sleeping with the rubircs last semester without any exaggeration.

I had her for two courses last semester, ADM3319 and ADM 4338. It was definitely horrible to see all the rubrics cause they were long and not to the point. There were two rubrics for the project and the presn and they were almost the same. Her ppt made me don't know where to begin to take notes. Important contents were missing, lack of illustration

rComments: Honestly, she's a nice lady. You can see that she cares. But some people are just not meant to be professors. She's incredibly forgetful and I've never, ever taken a more confusing and disorganized class. Rubrics are impossible to follow and she'll give you varying instructions which makes doing projects so much more stressful than necessary

Don't take ADM3319 with ANYONE else!! She makes her powerpoints extremely informative so you won't have to read a textbook and her lectures are always really interactive and relaxing. Her grading was really fair and she was always willing to go above and beyond for her students by answering questions and giving feedback.

I loved the class and Professor O'Sullivan ensured the progress of EACH student! She was extremely punctual when it came to responding to emails and always was open-minded when it came to discussing marks. She will always ensure 110% in her classes and genuinely CARES about her students. I learnt so much with her! Would take another class with her!

I have had her twice now. She is knowledgeable but she is all over the place. Her slides, syllabus, lectures, etc. I found that I was also confused in both of her classes. The best description i can give is - scattered. Overall you can figure out what she wants you to do for the group project, just do that. Goodluck on her exams....

I had her for two separate courses in one semester. Her lectures are long and boring. Everything she posts is impossible to follow, whether it be her slides, course syllabus and/or rubrics. Gives feedback but nitpicks everything. You'll likely have a 40 minute group presentation to do. She's smart but really irritating.

Her instructions are so detailed and nitpicky that you get confused and never know what to expect Did not learn anything with her, her focus was on sustainability whereas training and development should've been emphasised more  Midterm was not fair and way too hard

So vague on her rubrics for the group project. Then when you ask for help she becomes condescending. She is very  petty when it comes to grading. Writes comments about what word would have sounded better and docks marks. Her classes are so boring and for someone teaching about Training and how to engage new hires; it's irony at its best.

Her midterm exam is quite difficult (the multiple choice) - study the slides a lot. I found her lectures extremely boring, but if you pay attention then studying for the midterm is easier. Ask her questions, she provides really detailed answers over email. Especially helpful for paper & presentation. She grades the presentation pretty easy. :)

She is the most inspiring professor I have ever got a chance to be taught by. If you listen carefully what she has to say there will be no problems with this calss. Other comments are absolutely useless, just a bunch of angry students... Take her calsses and enjoy, talk and interact with this knowlegable and inspiring woman.
She just angers me, the expectations are not clear for the assignments, there is WAY TOO much group work!!!!!!!

Just like the last comment, she expects you to bring a note or contact her by email if you are going to leave early, even if it's for COOP or WORK! Even if it's leaving 5 minutes early! Extremely baised when marking, don't get on her bad sad, you're screw

Didn't know you had to ask to go to the bathroom in University??  Don't dare leave her class in the middle, she'll chase after you..but you'll fall asleep while she reads the slides, NOT accommodating and NOT helpful, doesn't care
